            "content": "Danish component = English meaning (use these to decode any unknown DMR field name):\n\nKoeretoej         = Vehicle\nOplysning         = Information (usually technical vehicle information)\nGrundStruktur     = Basic structure (root object for main technical data)\nBetegnelse        = Designation (make/model/type/variant hierarchy)\nMaerke / Mærke   = Make / brand (shown to users as brand name)\nModel             = Vehicle model designation\nVariant           = Model/approval variant\nArt               = Vehicle category (Personbil, Varebil, Motorcykel, etc.)\nAnvendelse        = Use/application (private, commercial, taxi, rental)\nRegistrering      = Registration\nRegistreringNummer = Registration number / licence plate\nStelNummer        = VIN / chassis number (sensitive — avoid public display)\nMotor             = Engine / motor (covers both combustion and electric)\nDrivmiddel/Drivkraft = Fuel / propulsion → use _drivkraft_primaer for dashboards\nMiljoeOplysning   = Environmental information (emissions, CO2, particles, filter)\nSynResultat       = Inspection result (roadworthiness)\nTilladelse        = Permit / permission / exemption\nKarrosseri        = Body / bodywork (body style type)\nUdstyr            = Equipment (standard or extra)\nVaegt / Vægt      = Weight (kg)\nAksel             = Axle (axle count, load, wheelbase, track width)\nSiddepladser      = Seats (min/max seat count)\nStoerste          = Maximum / largest\nEffekt            = Power / effect (kW)\nSlagVolumen       = Engine displacement (cc/cm³)\nHastighed         = Speed (km/h)\nCylinderAntal     = Cylinder count\nKilometerstand    = Odometer reading (km, but unit/scaling unverified in this dataset)\nFoerste           = First\nFarveType         = Colour type\nKarrosseriType    = Body style type\nTypeNummer/Num    = Numeric category code (NOT a metric — treat as identifier)\nIdent             = Identifier / ID (treat as categorical, not a measure)\nDato              = Date