            "path": "/skills/DMR Domain Knowledge/data-quality/data-quality.md",
            "content": "Known corrupt values — always apply these guards:\n- Power kW above 750: corrupt outliers. Use CLAMP(field, 0, 750) or WHERE field < 750.\n- Top speed km/h above 400: corrupt. Cap at 400.\n- Door count 0, 1, 8, 44: corrupt. Filter to WHERE field BETWEEN 2 AND 6.\n- First registration year beyond current year: future-dated imports. Cap with DATE_EXTRACT('year', NOW()).\n- Braked towing weight above 40,000 kg: extreme outlier. Cap at 40,000 for analytics.\n- Body style: can be NULL on some Personbil records — GROUP BY produces a null bucket, label it 'unknown'.\n- Colour 'Ukendt': means unknown/unrecorded, not a real colour — exclude or label explicitly.\n- EV electricity consumption field: unit-inconsistent/noisy — do not use in public tools.\n- Fuel label 'El': means fully electric only. No separate plug-in hybrid label — 'El/benzin' is the hybrid.\n- Fuel label 'Brint': hydrogen fuel cell vehicles.\n\nDefault scope for 'cars': KoeretoejArtNavn.keyword == 'Personbil' AND KoeretoejRegistreringStatus.keyword == 'Registreret'.\nTotal registered passenger-car count: 2,935,158 (validated 2026-05-09 from dmr-car-fleet-overview).\n- Seat count (KoeretoejOplysningSiddepladserMinimum): values 0 and above 9 are corrupt. Filter to WHERE field BETWEEN 1 AND 9. Approximately 161,203 records have missing or invalid seat count.\n- First registration year lower bound: values below 1900 are corrupt data entry errors (e.g. year 1086 for Volkswagen). Always add AND _foerste_registrering_aar >= 1900 for oldest-brand or heritage queries.\n- Inspection outcome labels in live data are NOT the human-readable Danish labels. The correct live labels are: Godkendt (approved), KanGodkendesVedOmsynAfOmsynsvirksomhed (conditional, re-inspection at approved body), KanGodkendesVedOmsynAfSynsvirksomhed (conditional, re-inspection at inspection station), IkkeGodkendt (failed), IkkeGodkendtKanGenfremstilles (failed, can be re-presented), IkkeFuldstaendigtSyn (incomplete). The old labels Betinget godkendt and Afvist match zero records.\n- For individual ranked list tools (power-to-weight list, high-power list), CLAMP must not be used — it makes corrupt values appear as plausible top entries. Use CASE to return NULL for out-of-range values and filter with WHERE field IS NOT NULL instead.\n- Average displacement in decade profiles: the query excludes displacement <= 50 cc, so the avg cc figure describes the ICE-valid subset, not all vehicles in that decade. EVs are effectively excluded from the displacement average.\n- taxi_suitable (KoeretoejOplysningEgnetTilTaxi): This is a TYPE-APPROVAL flag meaning the vehicle specifications are approved for taxi operation — it does NOT mean the vehicle currently operates as a taxi. 170,246 cars have this flag; only 5,090 are actually registered with usage \"Taxikørsel\". For current taxis use: WHERE usage == \"Taxikørsel\".\n- km_per_liter for EVs: ALL electric vehicles have a km_per_liter value (~67 km/L average). This is an energy-equivalent figure, not real fuel consumption. For meaningful ICE fuel efficiency comparisons: WHERE fuel != \"El\" AND km_per_liter > 1 AND km_per_liter <= 30. The flat view has km_per_liter (ICE only, 1-30 range) and km_per_liter_ev (EV range, 10-200) as separate columns.\n- awd column has corrupt values beyond 1 and 2: 0 (216 cars), 3 (35), 4 (1,615), 5 (27), 12 (104), 14 (14). The flat view now filters these to NULL. Use awd == 2 for AWD, awd == 1 for FWD/RWD — never awd >= 2.\n- body_style is NULL for 14.3% of cars (419,629), predominantly older petrol (331K) and diesel (88K) vehicles. Add WHERE body_style IS NOT NULL for clean body-style breakdown queries.\n- Brand case: 98.5% of brands are uppercase; 1.5% (44,149 cars) are mixed-case including Polestar (13,917), Cupra (11,610), Xpeng (7,759), Aiways (1,497), Leapmotor (436), Voyah (173), KG Mobility (154), Mercedes-AMG (148), Lynk & Co (250). Use TO_UPPER(brand) for case-insensitive matching.",
