t_start_date / permit_end_date — Permit validity dates when recorded.\n\nTECHNICAL NUMERIC (NULL = missing/corrupt/out-of-range, already guarded):\n  power_kw — Engine power in kW. Valid range 1-750. hp = kW * 1.36.\n  speed_kmh — Certified top speed in km/h. Valid range 50-400.\n  kerb_kg — Minimum kerb/running-order weight in kg. Valid range 300-5000.\n  max_kerb_kg — Raw maximum kerb/running-order weight in kg. Sanity-filter before rankings or averages.\n  gross_kg — Gross vehicle weight in kg. Valid range 300-10000.\n  own_kg — Own/empty vehicle weight in kg. Valid range 300-5000.\n  technical_gross_kg — Raw technically allowed total weight in kg. Sanity-filter before rankings or averages.\n  gross_combination_kg — Raw total permitted vehicle+trailer combination weight in kg. Sanity-filter before rankings or averages.\n  towing_kg — Braked towing capacity in kg. Valid range 1-5000.\n  unbraked_towing_kg — Unbraked towing capacity in kg. Valid range 1-5000.\n  doors — Door count. Valid range 2-6.\n  seats — Minimum seat count. Valid range 1-9.\n  max_seats — Raw maximum seat count. Sanity-filter before rankings or averages.\n  axles — Axle count. Valid range 1-10.\n  gears — Gear count. Valid range 1-12.\n  wheelbase_mm — Wheelbase in mm. Valid range 1500-4500.\n  front_track_mm / rear_track_mm — Raw track width in mm. Sanity-filter before rankings or averages.\n  cylinders — Engine cylinder count. 0 may mean electric.\n  displacement_cc — Engine displacement in cc. 0 for EVs.\n\nENVIRONMENT / EFFICIENCY:\n  co2_gkm — CO2 emissions in g/km. Never derive CO2 from fuel economy.\n  measurement_norm — WLTP/NEDC measurement standard.\n  emission_norm — Compatibility alias for measurement_norm. Do not use as Euro class.\n  euro_norm — Euro/environmental emissions norm/class.\n  particle_filter — Diesel particle-filter registry flag.\n  km_per_liter — ICE fuel economy only, range 1-30.\n  km_per_liter_ev — Energy-equivalent km/L for all cars, range 10-200.\n\nODOMETER:\